<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="3" pageNumber="16">
*Note: according to descriptions (antegenicular denticle and genicular denticle have not been separated) and drawings of 
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng, ZM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Shaanxi Normal University (Natural Science Edition)" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" pagination="12 - 17" title="Revision of the genus Hyboella Hancock from China (Tetrigoidea: Metrodoridae)." volume="30" year="2002">Zheng et al. (2002)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng, ZM" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" title="Fauna of Tetrigoidea from Western China." year="2005">Zheng (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, the type specimen (only one female) of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettixoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macromotettixoides aelytra" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelytra">Macromotettixoides aelytra</taxonomicName>
(Zheng, Li &amp; Shi, 2002) (synonym: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Hyboella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyboella aelytra" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelytra">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="17" start="start">Hyboella</pageBreakToken>
aelytra
</taxonomicName>
Zheng, Li &amp; Shi, 2002 (
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng, ZM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Huazhong Agricultural University" pageId="9" pageNumber="22" pagination="603 - 605" title="A revision of Macromotettixoides Zheng from China (Orthoptera: Metrodoridae)." volume="25" year="2006">Zheng et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
)) should be a nymph. Validity of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettixoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macromotettixoides aelytra" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelytra">Macromotettixoides aelytra</taxonomicName>
requires more material to confirm its characters, and herein we temporarily place the species in the key.
</paragraph>
